---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const lastUpdated = "March 1, 2025";
---

<Base
  title="Terms of Service | Chicago Vending Co."
  description="Chicago Vending Co. terms of service — the terms and conditions governing use of our website and vending services."
  canonical="https://chicagovendingco.com/terms"
>
  <Nav />
  <main class="legal-page">
    <div class="container legal-container">
      <div class="legal-header">
        <div class="legal-label">Legal</div>
        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-body">
        <p class="legal-intro">These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of the Chicago Vending Co. website and any vending services we provide. By using our website or services, you agree to these Terms. If you do not agree, please do not use our website or services.</p>

        <h2>1. Services Overview</h2>
        <p>Chicago Vending Co. provides vending machine placement, stocking, and maintenance services to qualifying commercial locations in the Chicago metropolitan area. Our services include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Installation and placement of vending machines at your location</li>
          <li>Regular restocking of machines with products</li>
          <li>Maintenance and repair of machines</li>
          <li>Cashless payment system operation</li>
          <li>Micro-market installation and operation</li>
          <li>Coffee machine installation and service</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. Service Eligibility</h2>
        <p>To qualify for our free vending placement program, your location must:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Have a minimum of 25 daily users (employees, students, patients, etc.)</li>
          <li>Be located within approximately 50 miles of downtown Chicago</li>
          <li>Provide adequate electrical access (standard 110V outlet)</li>
          <li>Provide adequate floor space for machine placement</li>
          <li>Be an indoor, climate-controlled environment</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Chicago Vending Co. reserves the right to decline service at its discretion and to remove machines from locations that no longer meet minimum usage thresholds.</p>

        <h2>3. Free Placement Agreement</h2>
        <p>Under our standard free placement program:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Chicago Vending Co. owns all machines placed at your location</li>
          <li>You pay no installation, maintenance, or service fees</li>
          <li>Chicago Vending Co. retains all revenue from product sales</li>
          <li>Revenue sharing may be available for qualifying high-volume locations (discussed at time of agreement)</li>
          <li>You provide reasonable access to machines for restocking and service</li>
          <li>You agree not to tamper with, relocate, or damage machines</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Service Level Agreement</h2>
        <p>Chicago Vending Co. provides the following service commitments:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Response time:</strong> We will respond to reported machine malfunctions within 4 hours during standard business hours (Monday–Friday, 8am–8pm CT)</li>
          <li><strong>SLA remedy:</strong> If we fail to respond within 4 hours, you will receive one month of service at no cost (applicable to locations that pay service fees)</li>
          <li><strong>Restocking:</strong> Machines will be restocked on a schedule determined by usage patterns, typically weekly</li>
          <li><strong>Emergency service:</strong> 24-hour emergency response available for healthcare and critical facilities</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Your Responsibilities</h2>
        <p>As a location host, you agree to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide unobstructed access to machines for service visits</li>
          <li>Notify us promptly of machine malfunctions, damage, or vandalism</li>
          <li>Not allow tampering with machines, including attempts to access internal components</li>
          <li>Not place competing vending machines within close proximity without notifying us</li>
          <li>Maintain the area around machines in a clean and safe condition</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Product Selection</h2>
        <p>Chicago Vending Co. determines the product mix in machines based on location type, sales data, and customer preferences. We will make reasonable accommodations for specific product requests but cannot guarantee the continuous availability of any specific product due to supply chain factors.</p>

        <h2>7. Payment Processing</h2>
        <p>All cashless payments processed through our machines are handled by third-party payment processors. By using our payment terminals, users agree to the terms of those payment processors. Chicago Vending Co. is not responsible for payment processing errors or unauthorized transactions initiated by third parties.</p>

        <h2>8. Liability Limitations</h2>
        <p>Chicago Vending Co.'s liability for any claim arising from our services is limited to the value of services provided in the 3 months preceding the claim. We are not liable for indirect, consequential, or incidental damages. We are not responsible for personal injury or property damage resulting from misuse of vending machines.</p>

        <h2>9. Termination</h2>
        <p>Either party may terminate a service agreement with 30 days written notice. Upon termination, Chicago Vending Co. will remove all machines from your premises within 14 business days. You agree to provide reasonable access for machine removal.</p>

        <h2>10. Website Use</h2>
        <p>You may use our website for lawful purposes only. You agree not to use our website to transmit harmful, offensive, or illegal content; attempt to gain unauthorized access to our systems; or interfere with the proper functioning of our website. We reserve the right to block access to users who violate these terms.</p>

        <h2>11. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>All content on the Chicago Vending Co. website — including text, images, logos, and design — is owned by or licensed to Chicago Vending Co. and protected by applicable copyright and trademark laws. You may not reproduce, distribute, or create derivative works without our express written permission.</p>

        <h2>12. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Illinois. Any disputes arising from these Terms or our services will be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts located in Cook County, Illinois.</p>

        <h2>13. Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p>We may update these Terms from time to time. We will provide 30 days notice of material changes to existing service customers. Continued use of our services after the effective date of changes constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.</p>

        <h2>14. Contact</h2>
        <div class="legal-contact">
          <p><strong>Chicago Vending Co.</strong></p>
          <p>350 N Orleans St, Suite 9000 · Chicago, IL 60654</p>
          <p>Email: <a href="mailto:legal@chicagovendingco.com">legal@chicagovendingco.com</a></p>
          <p>Phone: <a href="tel:+13125550190">(312) 555-0190</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="legal-nav">
        <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy →</a>
        <a href="/contact">Contact Us →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>

<style>
  .legal-page{padding:120px 0 100px;min-height:80vh}
  .legal-container{max-width:800px}
  .legal-label{font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--c-orange);font-weight:500;margin-bottom:14px}
  .legal-header{margin-bottom:48px;padding-bottom:32px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--c-border)}
  .legal-header h1{font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:clamp(36px,6vw,72px);font-weight:400;margin-bottom:10px}
  .legal-meta{font-size:14px;color:rgba(248,245,240,.4)}
  .legal-intro{font-size:17px;color:rgba(248,245,240,.8);line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:36px;padding:20px 24px;background:var(--c-dark);border-left:3px solid var(--c-orange);border-radius:0 var(--radius-lg) var(--radius-lg) 0}
  .legal-body h2{font-family:var(--font-display);font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,36px);font-weight:400;margin:48px 0 14px}
  .legal-body h3{font-size:17px;font-weight:500;margin:28px 0 10px;color:rgba(248,245,240,.9)}
  .legal-body p{font-size:15px;color:rgba(248,245,240,.72);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:16px}
  .legal-body ul{margin:0 0 20px 20px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:8px}
  .legal-body li{font-size:15px;color:rgba(248,245,240,.72);line-height:1.7}
  .legal-body a{color:var(--c-orange);text-decoration:underline;text-underline-offset:3px}
  .legal-body strong{color:var(--c-white);font-weight:500}
  .legal-contact{background:var(--c-dark);border:1px solid var(--c-border);border-radius:var(--radius-lg);padding:24px;margin-top:8px}
  .legal-contact p{margin-bottom:6px;font-size:15px;color:rgba(248,245,240,.72)}
  .legal-contact p:last-child{margin-bottom:0}
  .legal-nav{display:flex;gap:24px;margin-top:48px;padding-top:24px;border-top:1px solid var(--c-border)}
  .legal-nav a{font-size:14px;color:var(--c-orange);font-weight:500}
</style>
